article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 59, Wagner 57
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Fairleigh Dickinson 59, Wagner 57, OT. NEW YORK -- Terence Grier's 3-pointer at the overtime buzzer gave Fairleigh Dickinson a 59-57 victory over Wagner on Thursday night, the Seahawks' sixth straight loss. The Knights (6-17, 5-7 Northeast Conference) led 49-33 with 10:08 to play when Wagner (10-12, 3-9) went on a 16-0 run to tie the game and force overtime. Jamal Smith's layup with 15 seconds remaining made it 49-49 and capped the big run. Eric Moore of the Knights missed a 3-point attempt at the regulation buzzer. Alvin Mofunyana's layup 30 seconds into overtime ended the Knights' 10:38 scoring drought and made it 51-49. Smith's two free throws started an 8-1 run that gave the Seahawks a 57-52 lead. FDU closed the game on a 7-0 run, capped by Grier?s game-winner. Mofunyana, Moore and Sean Baptiste all scored 13 points for the Knights. Justin Drummond had 15 points for Wagner and Joey Mundweiler added 11.
